&lt;p&gt;Do you have senior administration expereince, worked for the NHS or looking to gain NHS experience?  Working for the Surrey and Borders NHS partnership Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a great opportunity for a senior administrator working at Forensic Outreach and Liaison Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for 3-4 months temp position, full time working monday to friday 9-5pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be managing a small team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Overview To act as the admin lead for the team ensuring day to day supervision of band 2 and 3 administrators workload.  Providing supervision and development to other members of the administration team in conjunction with Band 5 administrators, where appropriate.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working for Unither House is located in central Chertsey and is the main base for community services in North West Surrey. The building provides for the needs of people who use our services, carers and staff, with a range of consulting and group rooms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Services in Unither House&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arts Therapies: North West&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CAMHS ADHD &amp; ASD: ASPH&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CAMHS Community Team North West: Chertsey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Mental Health Recovery Service: Runnymede and Spelthorne&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Mental Health Team for Older People: Runnymede and West Elmbridge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Mental Health Team for Older People: Woking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Team for people with Learning Disabilities West: Chertsey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dialectical Behaviour Therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Early Intervention in Psychosis Service: West Surrey &amp; NE Hants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forensic Outreach and Liaison Service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mindful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mind Matters (previously Improving Access to Psychological Therapies - IAPT)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perinatal Mental Health Service: North West&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Psychotherapy: North West Surrey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other services may hold clinics and therapy sessions here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Getting to Unither House&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unither House is located close to public transport and the town centre. Chertsey station is a five minute walk and the nearest bus stops are a one minute walk away. There is parking for staff and visitors, plus there is a public car park located next door.&lt;/p&gt;
